H0.text: Who was the UK Poet Laureate or the longest period. John Dryden

H1.text: Who was the UK Poet Laureate or the longest period. Robert Bridges

H2.text: Who was the UK Poet Laureate or the longest period. William Wordsworth

H3.text: Who was the UK Poet Laureate or the longest period. Tennyson

A4.text: He held the position until his death in 1892, the longest tenure of any laureate.

A5.text: In 1850, after Wordsworth's death and Samuel Rogers' refusal, Tennyson was appointed Poet Laureate; Elizabeth Barrett Browning and Leigh Hunt had also been considered.
